Package ca.phon.app.session.editor

Class EditorEventType

java.lang.Object
ca.phon.app.session.editor.EditorEventType
public class EditorEventType
extends java.lang.Object
The class holds the event names that are sent by the editor model while the editor is displayed.

    • MODIFICATION_EVENT

      public static final java.lang.String MODIFICATION_EVENT
      Modification event. Any event which starts with '_x_' will set the modified flag. This is a generic event that should only be used when all other events do not apply or when a new event is needed by a module.

    • TIER_CHANGED_EVT

      public static final java.lang.String TIER_CHANGED_EVT
      Changes in tier data. Unlike TierListeners, this event is only called after focus has changed in a component. This is useful for view which should not update data as it is typed into editor fields. To listen for tier changes as they occur, use TierListeners instead. data: the tier name - String
      See Also:
